              "answers": {
                "answer_3": {
                  "score": 0.0,
                  "response": "Consider This: Most European nations recognized Huerta, however Wilson, calling him a “butcher,” refused. Instead, he announced a new policy: To win American recognition, revolutionary regimes in Latin America must not only exercise power but also be “a just government based upon law, not upon arbitrary or irregular force.” See L.O. 24.2 Foreign Policy Under Wilson."
